urteen months' ethnographic research with young men from middle caste Hindu, Muslim, and ex-Untouchable backgrounds. In addition to offering a new perspective on how education affects the rural poor in South Asia, Degrees Without Freedom? includes in-depth reflection on the politics of modernity, changing rural masculinities, and caste and communal politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aAnthropology -- Asia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aSociology -- Global Issues, Economy, and Work. 7aEDUCATION / Student Life & Student Affairs.2bisacsh1 aJeffery, Patricia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJeffery, Roger, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476842940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804768429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804768429/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles